	<description>Version 1.4
    In vanilla RimWorld, human-like pawns that are not part of your colony have a chance to instantly die when downed. Animals have a 50% chance to die when downed.
	
This chance changes depending on the storyteller, current colony population, and difficulty. These settings can be adjusted through the storyteller options in RimWorld 1.3 and later, but this mod gives you more options to tailor the death-on-down chance for both pawns and animals at any point during a play through.</description>
